{
  "texts": [
    "Consider the irregular class Θ = ⟨z 3 /3⟩.",
    "Its Stokes structure is trivial (there are no Stokes arrows).",
    "In turn, a wild character variety with this irregular class is nonempty only if its formal monodromy is the identity, so there exists a unique rank one Stokes local system V with irregular class Θ.",
    "Let us determine its Fourier transform.",
    "The formal Fourier transform of Θ is Θ = ⟨ 2 3 w 3/2 ⟩, which is closely related to the Airy differential equation."
  ]
}